<p><span style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-weight: normal;"><img height="72" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Pathway/who.png" width="709" /></span></p>
<h3><strong>Pathway is available to members of the Church who:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Are 18 to 30 years old (31+ program in some locations)</li>
<li>Have daily access to a computer with high-speed Internet</li>
<li>Are proficient in listening to, reading, writing, and speaking English*</li>
<li>Strive to live by BYU-Idaho's Honor Code</li>
<li>Are willing to attend a weekly gathering during the first year of the program</li>
</ul>
<p><em><span style="font-style: normal;"><em>*Language proficiency assessment may be required for non-native English speakers.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="x35869.xml">English Language Resources</a></em></span></em></p>
<ul>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 19px;"><strong><img height="72" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Pathway/apply1.png" width="709" /></strong></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 19px;"><strong> </strong></span></span></p>
<h3><strong>Complete the following steps to apply for Pathway:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<p><strong><a href="x40412.xml" target="_blank">STEP 1: Find Your Pathway Site</a></strong><br /> Pathway is offered in nearly 100 locations worldwide. See if there is a site near you.</p>
<p><strong><a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Pathway Application Tutorial.pdf" target="_blank">STEP 2: Review Application Tutorial</a></strong><br /> This tutorial walks students through every step of the Pathway application process. Prospective students should thoroughly review the training prior to applying. <br /> <strong><br /> <a href="http://www.besmart.com/" target="_blank">STEP 3: Apply to the Pathway Program</a></strong><br /> All students, regardless of which university they apply to, use the same application located at <em>www.besmart.com</em>. The tutorial notes which sections pertain to Pathway applicants.</p>
<p>If Pathway isn't what you are looking for, click <a href="http://www.byui.edu/admissions/enrollment-options">here</a> for information about other BYU-Idaho enrollment options.</p>
</ul>
<ol> </ol>
